---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { reports } from '../data/reports';
import { useCases } from '../data/useCases';
import { comparatorRows, competitors } from '../data/comparator';

const cellSymbol = (v: 'yes' | 'partial' | 'no') => v === 'yes' ? '●' : v === 'partial' ? '◐' : '○';
const cellClass = (v: 'yes' | 'partial' | 'no') => v === 'yes' ? 'yes' : v === 'partial' ? 'partial' : 'no';

const products = [
  { name: 'Sales Cloud',         status: 'live' },
  { name: 'Service Cloud',       status: 'live' },
  { name: 'Marketing Cloud',     status: 'live' },
  { name: 'Data Cloud',          status: 'live' },
  { name: 'Revenue Cloud (CPQ)', status: 'live' },
  { name: 'Field Service',       status: 'live' },
  { name: 'Experience Cloud',    status: 'live' },
  { name: 'Spiff (Comp)',        status: 'live' },
  { name: 'Health Cloud',        status: 'beta' },
  { name: 'Financial Services Cloud', status: 'beta' },
  { name: 'Manufacturing Cloud', status: 'beta' },
  { name: 'CG Cloud',            status: 'beta' },
  { name: 'Education Cloud',     status: 'beta' },
  { name: 'Agentforce',          status: 'beta' },
  { name: 'Tableau',             status: 'soon' },
  { name: 'MuleSoft',            status: 'soon' },
];
---
<Base active="home">

<header class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-tagline mono">$ rosetta scan --org you-just-inherited<span class="blink"></span></div>
    <h1>We speak <span class="grad">your org's language.</span></h1>
    <p class="lede">Rosetta is the AI-native Salesforce delivery stack — from org discovery through deploy. Twelve exec-grade analysis reports, industry-calibrated process mining, an end-to-end Scope → SOW → Config → UAT loop, all driven by Cursor. Built by Customertimes, the SI that runs the engagement.</p>
    <div class="ctas">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#contact">Book a 4-hour scan</a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="#comparator">See it vs. the competition</a>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-stats">
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">4–6 hr</div><div class="lbl">From OAuth to 12 finished reports</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">12</div><div class="lbl">Distinct AI analyses per scan</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">90%</div><div class="lbl">Discovery time eliminated vs. manual sprint</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">∞</div><div class="lbl">LLM choice — Cursor-native, MCP-flexible</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- THE THESIS -->
<section id="thesis">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">The thesis</div>
      <h2>Discovery isn't a tool. <br/>It's the first step of the delivery loop.</h2>
      <p>Every competitor in this space stops somewhere: Hubbl ends at documentation. Apromore at process mining. Sweep at a visual canvas and a beta "build mode." Saltbox at admin-as-code. Swantide at admin productivity. Rosetta is the only platform that closes the loop — discovery, scope, design, config, UAT — and is the only one open enough to ride Cursor's roadmap instead of competing with it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="legs">
      <div class="leg">
        <div class="num">// 01</div>
        <h3>Deeper than discovery</h3>
        <p>Twelve distinct AI analyses. Exec-grade, opinionated, industry-calibrated, ROI-quantified. The reports a Big-4 partner would charge $250K to produce, generated in hours.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="leg">
        <div class="num">// 02</div>
        <h3>End-to-end, not one slice</h3>
        <p>Discovery → Scope → SOW → Config → UAT → Training. Scope decisions carry forward into the build via a versioned crosswalk. The same platform delivers what discovery uncovers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="leg">
        <div class="num">// 03</div>
        <h3>Built on Cursor, not against it</h3>
        <p>Sweep's moat depends on its agentic IDE staying proprietary. Ours compounds with Cursor's. Every Cursor release upgrades Rosetta. MCP-native. Open LLM. No vendor lock-in.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ARCHITECTURE -->
<section id="architecture">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">The architecture</div>
      <h2>Two layers. One substrate.</h2>
      <p>Rosetta is split into the layer that reads your org, the layer that changes it, and the open substrate they both run on.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="arch">
      <div class="col">
        <h3>Discovery Layer</h3>
        <h4>Read the org. Quantify the truth.</h4>
        <p>Ingests Salesforce metadata + event logs and produces twelve exec-grade reports, industry-calibrated.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Executive Brief (A–F grading)</li>
          <li>Tech Debt + Code Quality</li>
          <li>Process Mining (BPMN / CMMI)</li>
          <li>Security · Integration · License</li>
          <li>Dependency graph + blast radius</li>
          <li>Delta scans (continuous)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col">
        <h3>Delivery Layer</h3>
        <h4>Change the org. Carry decisions through.</h4>
        <p>Generates Scope Builder, SOW, Configuration Template, and executes CLI-based configuration with diff review.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>AI Scope Builder + SOW generator</li>
          <li>Configuration Template w/ crosswalk</li>
          <li>Implementation Playbook (per product)</li>
          <li>CLI-driven config via Cursor</li>
          <li>UAT Tracker</li>
          <li>Training Guide on handoff</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col">
        <h3>Configuration Library</h3>
        <h4>One playbook per Salesforce product.</h4>
        <p>Order-of-operations playbooks for every Salesforce product. Drop one in to run a fresh implementation end-to-end.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Sales · Service · Marketing</li>
          <li>Data Cloud · Revenue Cloud</li>
          <li>Industry Clouds (FSC / Health / Mfg / Edu)</li>
          <li>Field Service · Experience</li>
          <li>Spiff (Compensation)</li>
          <li>Agentforce · Tableau · MuleSoft</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="substrate">
        <div>
          <div class="lbl">SUBSTRATE</div>
          <div style="color:#fff;font-family:var(--display);font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:6px">Built on Cursor — MCP-native, BYO LLM, diff-reviewed</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cursor">
          <div class="logo">↗</div>
          <div>
            <div class="lbl">Strategic partnership</div>
            <div style="color:#fff;font-weight:700">Rosetta × Cursor</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="config-library">
      {products.map(p => (
        <div class="config-pill">
          <span class={`status ${p.status === 'beta' ? 'beta' : p.status === 'soon' ? 'soon' : ''}`}></span>
          <b>{p.name}</b>
          <span style="color:#5B6685;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.74rem;margin-left:auto">{p.status}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- COMPARATOR -->
<section id="comparator">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">The competitive read</div>
      <h2>Every other tool covers a slice. <br/>Rosetta covers the loop.</h2>
      <p>Click any row to filter the comparison. Capability × competitor — fully honest. Where competitors do something well, we mark it; where they don't, we mark that too.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="comparator">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Capability</th>
            {competitors.map(c => <th class={c === 'Rosetta' ? 'col-rosetta' : ''}>{c}</th>)}
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {comparatorRows.map(r => (
            <tr>
              <td>{r.capability}</td>
              <td class={cellClass(r.sweep)}>{cellSymbol(r.sweep)}</td>
              <td class={cellClass(r.hubbl)}>{cellSymbol(r.hubbl)}</td>
              <td class={cellClass(r.swantide)}>{cellSymbol(r.swantide)}</td>
              <td class={cellClass(r.apromore)}>{cellSymbol(r.apromore)}</td>
              <td class={cellClass(r.saltbox)}>{cellSymbol(r.saltbox)}</td>
              <td class={`col-rosetta ${cellClass(r.rosetta)}`}>{cellSymbol(r.rosetta)}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="mono" style="color:#5B6685;font-size:.85rem;margin-top:14px;text-align:center">● = full coverage&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;◐ = partial coverage&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;○ = not covered</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- USE CASES PREVIEW -->
<section id="use-cases">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">By use case</div>
      <h2>Eight ways to put Rosetta to work.</h2>
      <p>Each maps to a real artifact set already produced in client engagements. See all eight on the <a href="/features/">Features page →</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="use-cases">
      {useCases.slice(0,4).map(uc => (
        <a href={`/features/#${uc.id}`} class="uc" style="text-decoration:none">
          <span class="uc-num">{uc.num}</span>
          <div class="who">{uc.who}</div>
          <h3>{uc.title}</h3>
          <p>{uc.pitch}</p>
          <div class="meta"><span><b>In:</b> {uc.input}</span><span><b>Out:</b> {uc.output}</span></div>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
    <div style="text-align:center;margin-top:32px"><a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/features/">See all 8 use cases →</a></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- REPORT GALLERY -->
<section id="outputs">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">Sample outputs</div>
      <h2>The reports Rosetta actually produces.</h2>
      <p>Twelve distinct AI analyses per scan. Click any title to preview a real (sanitized) excerpt. Click the comparator row above to see which competitors ship which.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="report-gallery">
      <div class="report-list" id="report-list">
        {reports.map((r, i) => (
          <button data-id={r.id} class={i === 0 ? 'active' : ''}>
            <span class="num">{r.num}</span>
            <span>{r.title}</span>
          </button>
        ))}
      </div>
      <div class="report-pane">
        <div class="report-tabs">
          <span class="dot r"></span><span class="dot y"></span><span class="dot g"></span>
          <span class="title mono" id="report-filename">rosetta-report-01.md</span>
        </div>
        <div class="report-body" id="report-body">
          {/* JS will populate */}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- INTERACTIVE ESTIMATOR -->
<section id="estimator">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">Try it</div>
      <h2>What would Rosetta find in your org?</h2>
      <p>Slide the inputs to roughly match your org. We'll estimate where you'd land on a Rosetta tech-debt scorecard. Honest, illustrative — not a substitute for the real scan.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="estimator">
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-family:var(--mono);color:var(--brand-bright);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.12em;margin-bottom:20px">Your org · rough sizing</h3>
        <div class="form-row">
          <label for="e-apex">Apex classes</label>
          <input id="e-apex" type="range" min="0" max="2000" step="50" value="400" />
          <span class="val" id="e-apex-v">400</span>
        </div>
        <div class="form-row">
          <label for="e-flows">Flows</label>
          <input id="e-flows" type="range" min="0" max="500" step="5" value="80" />
          <span class="val" id="e-flows-v">80</span>
        </div>
        <div class="form-row">
          <label for="e-triggers">Triggers per object (max)</label>
          <input id="e-triggers" type="range" min="1" max="6" step="1" value="2" />
          <span class="val" id="e-triggers-v">2</span>
        </div>
        <div class="form-row">
          <label for="e-coverage">Apex test coverage %</label>
          <input id="e-coverage" type="range" min="50" max="100" step="1" value="80" />
          <span class="val" id="e-coverage-v">80%</span>
        </div>
        <div class="form-row">
          <label for="e-wf">Active Workflow Rules</label>
          <input id="e-wf" type="range" min="0" max="200" step="2" value="30" />
          <span class="val" id="e-wf-v">30</span>
        </div>
        <div class="form-row">
          <label for="e-old">Apex classes on API &lt; v55</label>
          <input id="e-old" type="range" min="0" max="200" step="5" value="20" />
          <span class="val" id="e-old-v">20</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="result" id="e-result">
        <div class="lbl">Estimated tech-debt grade</div>
        <div class="big" id="e-grade">B</div>
        <div class="mono" style="color:#C7D0EC;font-size:.92rem" id="e-score">76 / 100</div>
        <div class="ann" id="e-ann">Solid foundation with a few targeted cleanups. Run a real scan to find the named offenders.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CURSOR PARTNERSHIP -->
<section id="cursor">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">Strategic partnership</div>
      <h2>Rosetta × Cursor.</h2>
      <p>Cursor is the most rapidly-advancing AI development environment in the industry. Rosetta runs on it. That choice was deliberate — and structural.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="partnership">
      <div>
        <ul style="color:#C7D0EC;font-size:1rem;list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0">
          <li style="padding:14px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line-d);display:flex;gap:14px;align-items:flex-start"><span class="mono" style="color:var(--brand-bright);font-weight:700">01</span><div><b style="color:#fff">BYO LLM.</b> Claude, GPT, Gemini, your own — Rosetta swaps models without re-engineering. Sweep is locked.</div></li>
          <li style="padding:14px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line-d);display:flex;gap:14px;align-items:flex-start"><span class="mono" style="color:var(--brand-bright);font-weight:700">02</span><div><b style="color:#fff">MCP-native.</b> Connect any Model Context Protocol server. Salesforce, Snowflake, Jira, GitHub — first-class.</div></li>
          <li style="padding:14px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line-d);display:flex;gap:14px;align-items:flex-start"><span class="mono" style="color:var(--brand-bright);font-weight:700">03</span><div><b style="color:#fff">Diff-reviewed configuration.</b> Every change Rosetta proposes lands as a reviewable patch. Trust-level: developer.</div></li>
          <li style="padding:14px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line-d);display:flex;gap:14px;align-items:flex-start"><span class="mono" style="color:var(--brand-bright);font-weight:700">04</span><div><b style="color:#fff">Compounds with Cursor's roadmap.</b> Every Cursor release upgrades Rosetta. No moat to defend.</div></li>
          <li style="padding:14px 0;display:flex;gap:14px;align-items:flex-start"><span class="mono" style="color:var(--brand-bright);font-weight:700">05</span><div><b style="color:#fff">Open, not closed.</b> Sweep's deck argues "agentic partners will own the next decade." Agreed — and the most agentic substrate wins. That's Cursor.</div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="lock">
        <div class="logos">
          <div class="l cursor">→</div>
          <div class="x">×</div>
          <div class="l rosetta"><div style="width:18px;height:18px"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M12.7287 13.8233C12.7287 14.5839 12.7287 15.2627 12.7287 15.9476C10.0747 15.9476 8.72331 15.9354 4.88075 15.9476C1.89706 15.6553 -0.128024 12.7662 0.00630351 9.58886C0.14063 6.41969 2.41401 4.07656 6.04085 4.00091C6.1243 3.99886 17.7639 4.00091 24 4.00091C23.6702 4.76355 23.3833 5.42601 23.0617 6.1723C21.8406 6.1723 20.6357 6.1723 19.3534 6.1723C19.3534 9.4621 19.3534 12.6803 19.3534 15.9476C18.6188 15.9476 17.9655 15.9476 17.2164 15.9476C17.2164 12.7601 17.2164 9.46823 17.2164 6.1723C16.8074 6.14981 16.4837 6.1723 16.1602 6.1723C12.8386 6.16821 9.51707 6.16617 6.19553 6.1723C3.88143 6.17639 2.28376 7.63624 2.20438 9.78106C2.11483 12.1855 3.42757 13.6842 5.90652 13.8212C7.76268 13.9255 12.7938 13.8907 12.7287 13.8233Z" fill="white"/><path d="M19.4097 18.3594C19.4097 19.1977 19.4097 19.9603 19.4097 20.7863C14.4214 20.7863 9.49193 20.7863 4.46484 20.7863C4.46484 19.995 4.46484 19.2099 4.46484 18.3594C9.43088 18.3594 14.3603 18.3594 19.4097 18.3594Z" fill="white"/></svg></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="label">Strategic partnership</div>
        <h3 style="margin:6px 0 12px;font-size:1.3rem">Cursor × Customertimes</h3>
        <p class="strap">The fastest-moving AI dev environment, paired with the SI delivery muscle that turns it into outcomes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA -->
<section id="contact" class="cta-band band">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="eyebrow" style="color:#fff;opacity:.9">Next step</div>
    <h2>Connect an org. Get twelve reports back by end of day.</h2>
    <p>Read-only OAuth. No data leaves your control. Sanitized samples available on request. Customertimes signs an NDA before the scan kicks off.</p>
    <div class="ctas">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="mailto:rosetta@customertimes.com?subject=Rosetta%20%E2%80%94%20Request%20a%20scan">Book a 4-hour scan</a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/product/">See the product architecture →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script type="application/json" id="rosetta-reports-data" set:html={JSON.stringify(reports)}></script>
<script is:inline>
(function(){
  try {
    const el = document.getElementById('rosetta-reports-data');
    if (el) window.__ROSETTA_REPORTS__ = JSON.parse(el.textContent);
  } catch(e) {}
})();
</script>
<script type="module" src="/scripts/home.js"></script>

</Base>
